[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 2. `user=a35b2627f7084d26b3ff97a50e8c5a9d` - Session identifier              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m    - Random MD5-like hash (32 hex characters)                                [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m    - Used for user tracking                                                  [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Application Features:**                                                    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - Bookmark management system allowing users to add URLs with custom names    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - Bookmarks stored client-side in serialized cookie (not server-side)        [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - URL status checking functionality mentioned but not yet observed           [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - No authentication required - open access                                   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Critical Security Finding:**                                               [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m The application uses Python pickle serialization in the `bookmarks` cookie,  [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m creating a **confirmed insecure deserialization vulnerability**. The pickle  [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m format signature (`0x80 0x04`) is present and the cookie successfully        [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m unpickles to a Python list object.                                           [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ### **PROOFS**                                                               [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ```                                                                          [32m│[0m
